 To that effect, the CS ordered that starting today, all the police officers participating in the exercise be denied entry into exam centres if in possession of mobile phones.  “These mobile phones are being used to take screenshots of the test questions and intended to be sent to destinations that will facilitate cheating...” Onsati says not a single cheating incident has been reported in the country. Education CS says any centre found to engage in unethical practices will face stern action. Senate health team concludes probe, finds Jonah Manjari and five others have case to answer. Dr Philip Mpango will be sworn-in on Wednesday as Tanzania's new Vice President. Maritime security expert Dirk Siebels unpacks lessons learnt from the incident.